On another note, I hadn't seen a film before cultivating fondness for the German army and common folks, while trying to highlight that the opposing sides have more that unites than separates them.

2dd46660-7e58-4eeb-aaf5-3579af653d31.Notes: The ending is mindblowing. It lets the spectator decide what the verdict should be. Peter Lorre's monologue is chilling. The film's street and interiors' camera angles are ahead of their time and the dialogue can be easily used as is in a modern era movie. There are so many firsts in the history of cinema in the scenario and directing. Overall, a thrilling film to watch and especially its ending which I didn't expect at all.
